mild symptoms of acute mountain sickness.

82
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:04,920
There's also clinical relevance to
studying the body's response to hypoxic

83
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:10,120
conditions for example, people with
chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, and

84
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:13,280
heart disease, experience varying degrees
of hypoxia.

85
00:05:14,830 --> 00:05:18,990
Fetal development is also on the list
because under normal conditions,

86
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:24,270
the developing fetus en utero exists in a
hypoxic environment.

87
00:05:24,270 --> 00:05:28,820
Fetal arterial Oxygen tension is about one
quarter of a healthy adult.

88
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:32,540
So, 25 versus a 100 Torr respectively.

89
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:37,980
That is equivalent to the blood-Oxygen of
a person on the summit of Mount Everest.

90
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:40,790
